  "text": "18 We note that the conventions of [CITATION_1] are opposite to ours (the BPS localized D-branes in IIB theory are the A branes in [CITATION_2] ) because they consider the theory on the T-dual circle with a condensate of momentum. Indeed, in the exact conformal field theory, the choice of A-or Btype boundary condition is arbitrary, since they are related by an automorphism of the N = 2 superconformal algebra. It is only after we specify a specific semi-classical picture, i.e. give a geometrical interpretation to the N = 2 currents and the branes in the conformal field theory that the distinction between A-type and B-type branes becomes meaningful.",
